31/01/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- During a meeting with Romanian President Traian Basescu in Brussels on Tuesday (January 30th), European Commission President Jose Manuel Durao Barroso recommended that Romania work to boost its capacity to absorb EU funds. He stressed that Romania is to receive a total of 32 billion euros under various projects. In other news, Romania's Conservative Party said it was launching a petition drive for a parliamentary motion against Justice Minister Monica Macovei, accusing her of achieving poor results. (Gandul, Ziua - 31/01/07; Rompres, Mediafax - 30/01/07) 
